-- Scripps Networks in Talks to Buy Virgin's 50% Stake in UKTV, Journal Says
-- B y   V i v e k   S h a n k a r
-- 2010-12-15T01:26:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/scripps-networks-in-talks-to-buy-50-stake-in-uktv-wsj-says.html
Scripps Networks Interactive is in
talks to buy Virgin Media Inc.’s 50 percent stake in cable
operator UKTV for about $500 million, the Wall Street Journal
reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the matter.  UKTV is a joint venture between Virgin and BBC Worldwide,
according to the Journal.   An unidentified spokeswoman for Virgin declined to comment,
while Scripps didn’t respond to requests for comment, the
newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vivek Shankar at 
 vshankar3@bloomberg.net  